 *HOW TO START ON EXPRESS.JS*

- download and install node.js

- create a folder

- open it in vs code

- open the terminal and type "npm init -y"  to create packages including json file

- in the terminal, type "npm i -D nodemon"

- in package.json file, find "scripts" object and inside of it type
	"start": "node index",
	"dev": "nodemon index"
	- this would auto rerun node in every changes you make

- npm run dev, to start it

- terminal - "npm i body-parser"

- code on the top, let bodyParser = require('body-parser');

- after that, code:
	app.use(bodyParser.urlencoded({ extended: false }));
	app.use(bodyParser.json());